---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTAButton from "../components/CTAButton.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="New Rider — TT Motorcycle School"
  description="New to motorcycles? TT Motorcycle School guides complete beginners through everything they need to start riding safely in Sussex. Start with CBT."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Start Here</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">New to Riding?</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">
        You're in the right place. Whether you've never sat on a bike or you're
        just exploring whether motorcycling is for you, TT Motorcycle School
        will get you riding safely and confidently.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Where Do I Start?</h2>
        <p>
          If you're a complete beginner, the first step is your <strong
            >Compulsory Basic Training (CBT)</strong
          >. This is a legal requirement before you can ride on UK roads, and
          it's a brilliant foundation for everything that follows.
        </p>
        <p>
          At TT Motorcycle School we make the CBT a positive, enjoyable
          experience. You don't need any prior experience just a positive
          attitude and a willingness to learn.
        </p>

        <p>
          Included in the course price is: motorcycle or scooter hire,
          motorcycle safety clothing and a helmet.
        </p>

        <h2>What to Expect</h2>
        <p>Your CBT day covers five elements:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Introduction and eyesight check</strong> — a safety briefing and
            paperwork
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Practical on-site training</strong> — learning to control the
            bike in a safe, off-road environment
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Essential riding skills</strong> — braking, steering, gear changes
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>On-road training</strong> — riding on public roads with your instructor
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Certificate of completion</strong> — your DL196 certificate, valid
            for 2 years
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>What You'll Need</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>A valid UK driving licence or provisional licence</li>
          <li>
            To be at least 16 years old (mopeds) or 17 years old (motorcycles)
          </li>
          <li>
            Appropriate clothing — <a href="/what-to-wear/">see our guide</a>
          </li>
          <li>Glasses or contact lenses if required</li>
          <li>
            Able to ride a bicycle competently with good control and balance
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What Comes Next?</h2>
        <p>
          After your CBT, you can ride solo on a restricted machine. From there,
          many riders go on to their <a href="/full-licence/"
            >full motorcycle licence</a
          >. We'll guide you through every step of that journey too.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar__card">
          <h3 class="sidebar__title">Ready to Book?</h3>
          <p class="sidebar__body">
            CBT sessions fill up fast. Secure your spot online today.
          </p>
          <CTAButton
            href="/cbtbooking/"
            label="Book Your CBT"
            variant="accent"
            size="md"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar__card sidebar__card--plain">
          <h3 class="sidebar__title">Useful Links</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar__links">
            <li><a href="/cbt/">About CBT</a></li>
            <li><a href="/full-licence/">Full Licence Courses</a></li>
            <li><a href="/what-to-wear/">What to Wear</a></li>
            <li><a href="/prices/">View Prices</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact/">Ask a Question</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .content-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
    }
  }

  .sidebar__card {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .sidebar__card--plain {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .sidebar__title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .sidebar__body {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: #ccc;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .sidebar__links {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .sidebar__links a {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .sidebar__links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
